[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Candles in candelabras and incense burners stay lit forever instead of burning out, and removing them returns the candle or incense to your inventory so they stop being single-use.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Infinite burn[/b] — any candle slotted into a candelabra, and any incense placed in a burner, stays lit indefinitely. No re-fuelling, no replacement runs.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-lit on placement[/b] — placing a candle or incense immediately lights it. Skips the vanilla "standing there with a torch trying to light it" dance.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Extinguish and remove with a single key[/b] — default C on keyboard, Up on the D-Pad for candles (both rebindable). The candle returns to your inventory so you can move it to a different candelabra.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Separate incense keybind[/b] — unbound by default so candle-only players keep their existing experience. Set a key (or controller button) in the Controls section and it extinguishes the nearest lit incense and drops the unused incense back to you.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Interaction distance[/b] — configurable slider. Default is close-range so you don't accidentally snuff a distant candle or incense while walking.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Troubleshooting[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Can't demolish a church candelabra or incense burner?[/b] Extinguish it first with the relevant key. Lit candles and incenses count as "in use" to the game, which blocks demolish — the same rule that stops you from destroying a crafting station while a craft is in progress. Once extinguished, it can be demolished normally.[/size]
[/list]

